\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0       INVENTORY IMPROVEMENTS}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0       }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0       Over the years, we've added over 50 new recipes to the inventories of the various factions. Unfortunately, many of these new recipes were in places we hadn't previously checked. After much internal deliberation, we've decided to make these new recipes available to everyone. If you've discovered a new recipe, you can pick it up from the inventories of one of the factions in one of the following ways:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0       }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0       }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0        * By visiting one of the four gateways provided by the various Iron Horde factions (\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u239\'EF\u191\'BF\u189\'BD la [80] Path to Power).}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0        * By speaking with an NPC in one of the many capital cities (\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u239\'EF\u191\'BF\u189\'BD la [Paradise] or Bank of the Historian).}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0        * By visiting one of the many NPCs that give quests (\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u239\'EF\u191\'BF\u189\'BD la the "NPCs in the City").}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0        * By using the Quest Tracker located in the bottom right corner of the mini-map (\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u239\'EF\u191\'BF\u189\'BD la [Find A Grave]).}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0        * By using the Quick Join system, which is located in the bottom left corner of the mini-map, players can be automatically entered into group chats.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0        }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0        }
