\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0       GUILDS}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0       }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0       Guild creation is now in the game, but not quite as it was originally intended to be. Gone are the days when you could create a guild and call it whatever you wanted. You now required a 2-page application to be able to join a guild, and a 3-page application to be able to create a new guild. While we have made some improvements to the guild creation process, it is still not quite as simple as it was.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0       }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0       }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0       In order to make the guild experience more meaningful, we've made some changes to the guild experience itself. In particular, we've added a third step to becoming a member of a guild, the "Story Step." This third step allows a member of a guild to experience the full value of the experience bonus before deciding to join a guild, by providing a steady stream of bonus rewards for participating in a weekly bonus roll, and offers an incentive to continuing the guild regardless of whether you are a member of the guild or not.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0       }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0       }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0        * Each week, players will receive a new quest at a random location on the world, requiring them to complete a specific dungeon run in order to receive the "Story Reward" \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u226\'E2\u8364\'80\u8220\'93 a hefty 375% bonus to an item's drop rate!}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0        * The quest can be completed by all players who have attained a rating of Silver or higher in the respective role that week, but only a member of a guild will be eligible to receive the bonus.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0        * Completed dungeons will award bonus resources up to a maximum of 375% of the week's cap, with a weekly cap of 10,000 (up from 10,000).}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0        * Once a player has earned more than one story reward from a specific week during the same period, the player will receive an additional bonus roll for that week's reward.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0        * The final bonus roll reward will be based on the final rating of the guild that week, with a minimum cap of 1,000 for each guild.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0        * Once a player has earned more than one bonus roll during the same period, the player will receive an additional bonus roll for that week's reward.}
